  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Orthopedic implant wear-debris CFD credibility assessment (MRL 3)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD-based prediction of wear-particle transport and synovial fluid flow in a total knee replacement (TKR) joint space under physiological loading conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case wear-debris accumulation sites for a Class II orthopedic implant at Model Risk Level 3. Full 13-factor assessment: all factors addressed per MRL 3 requirements. Seven factors fully assessed with achievedLevel >= requiredLevel; six factors scoped-out with documented rationale consistent with MRL 3 scope. Sensitivity analysis performed over ±15% variation in synovial fluid viscosity and ±10% variation in implant gap geometry.",
